article.description: — Demetric Horton scored 26 points as North Carolina A&T defeated Presbyterian 65-57 on Wednesday night in a Big South Conference opener for both teams.
article.headline: Horton scores 26 to lead North Carolina A&T by Presbyterian
article.linkText: Horton scores 26 to lead North Carolina A&T by Presbyterian
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- — Demetric Horton scored 26 points as North Carolina A&T defeated Presbyterian 65-57 on Wednesday night in a Big South Conference opener for both teams. Horton hit 10 of 13 shots. Marcus Watson had 16 points and 11 rebounds for North Carolina A&T (6-9). David Beatty added 10 points. Winston Hill had 19 points for the Blue Hose (8-8). Trevon Reddish added 10 points and six rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
